.TH GHOSTBREW 1 "May 2026" "GhostBrew 0.3.2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ghostbrew \- GhostBrew support, benchmark, completion, and runtime front-end
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ghostbrew
.I COMMAND
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ghostbrew
provides a user-facing command surface for GhostBrew. It can launch the
underlying
.B scx_ghostbrew
scheduler, generate support bundles, run short benchmark workflows, and emit
shell completion scripts.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B run
Execute
.B scx_ghostbrew
and forward remaining arguments directly to the scheduler runtime.
.TP
.B support
Generate a support bundle under
.I ~/.local/state/ghostbrew/support/
by default. Use
.B --json
to also write a machine-readable JSON copy.
.TP
.B benchmark
Run a short benchmark workload while GhostBrew stats are collected, then write
text and JSON reports under
.I ~/.local/state/ghostbrew/benchmarks/
by default.
.TP
.B completions
Generate shell completions for bash, zsh, fish, and other supported shells.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/ghostbrew/config.toml
User configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/ghostbrew/profiles/
User profile directory.
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/ghostbrew/support/
Default support bundle output directory.
.TP
.I ~/.local/state/ghostbrew/benchmarks/
Default benchmark output directory.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR scx_ghostbrew (1)
